    public interface Wrapper
    Wrapper class that contains methods for unwrap objects obtaining a down casting objects from some given class.
    Since:
    1.0
    Author:
    Jose Zalacain
    See Also:
    AbstractWrapper

    • Method Detail

      • unwrap

        <K> K unwrap(Class<K> cls)
        Down cast the current wrapper object to specific given class. Call Wrapper#unwrap(Object, Class) passing like argument this instance and the given class. If down casting is not possible raise a RuntimeException.
        Type Parameters:
        K - type of object to be cast.
        Parameters:
        cls - class of K type to obtain a down cast.
        Returns:
        current instance of type cls.
        Throws:
        RuntimeException - if down casting is not possible
        Since:
        1.0
        See Also:
        unwrap(Object, Class)

      • unwrap

        <K> K unwrap(Object o,
             Class<K> cls)
        Down cast a given wrapper object to specific given class. If down casting is not possible raise a RuntimeException.
        Type Parameters:
        K - type of object to be cast.
        Parameters:
        o - object to be cast to K type instance
        cls - class of K type to obtain a down cast.
        Returns:
        current instance of type cls.
        Throws:
        RuntimeException - if down casting is not possible
        Since:
        1.0
        See Also:
        unwrap(Class)

      • isWrappedFor

        boolean isWrappedFor(Class<?> cls)
        Check if the current object can be down cast to an object of type cls class. More formally perform the boolean class method Class#isInstance(this).
        Parameters:
        cls - class of to obtain a down cast.
        Returns:
        true if the current object can be down cast to an object of type cls class, false if not
        Since:
        1.0
        See Also:
        unwrap(Class), unwrap(Object, Class), isWrappedFor(Object, Class)

      • isWrappedFor

        boolean isWrappedFor(Object o,
                     Class<?> cls)
        Check if the current object can be down cast to an object of type cls class. More formally perform the boolean class method Class#isInstance(o).
        Parameters:
        o - object to be check
        cls - class of to obtain a down cast.
        Returns:
        true if the current object can be down cast to an object of type cls class, false if not
        Since:
        1.0
        See Also:
        unwrap(Class), unwrap(Object, Class), isWrappedFor( Class)
